## 3. Selected MVP Concept

### 3.1 MVP Summary

**Flex Sight** is a simple embedded monitoring system designed to continuously measure temperature levels and support early safety alerts in operational environments. Temperature data is transmitted through MQTT/API to the server, where readings are processed and checked against a defined threshold. When the temperature reaches approximately **50°C**, the system automatically triggers an instant dashboard alert.

**Core workflow:** MQTT/API → Server → Dashboard Alert

### 3.2 Reasons for Selection

| Criteria | Justification |
|----------|--------------|
| Feasibility | Can be built using available hardware components and beginner-friendly software tools within the project timeline. |
| Simplicity | Clear and focused MVP workflow with no unnecessary complexity. |
| Technical Alignment | Fits the team's current skills in embedded systems, backend development, and dashboard design. |
| Scalability | Architecture supports future expansion with additional sensors, locations, and AI integration. |
| Real-World Impact | Directly addresses a safety problem in operational environments. |

### 3.3 Technical Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|-------|-----------|---------|
| Hardware | Arduino Uno + DHT11 Sensor | Continuously reads temperature data from the environment |
| Communication | MQTT / REST API | Lightweight, real-time data transmission from device to server |
| Backend / Server | Python (Flask) | Receives sensor data, processes readings, checks the 50°C threshold, manages alert logic |
| Database | SQLite | Stores temperature readings, alert logs, and device records |
| Frontend / Dashboard | HTML + CSS + JavaScript | Displays live readings, device status, and instant alerts |

### 3.4 Target Audience

| User Type | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| Facility Managers | Responsible for monitoring operational environments such as server rooms, warehouses, and factories. Need centralised visibility and instant alerts. |
| Safety Teams | Monitor dashboard alerts, respond to incidents, and make fast decisions based on real-time temperature data. |
| Technical Operators | Oversee device status, review historical readings, and ensure sensor calibration and system uptime. |
| Organisation Owners | Require high-level visibility of safety metrics and alert history across their facilities. |

### 3.5 Main Features

- Real-time temperature monitoring
- Automatic dashboard alerts when temperature reaches ~50°C
- MQTT/API communication between sensor and server
- Centralised monitoring interface with live readings
- Device status visibility
- Historical reading storage and logging
- Lightweight and scalable architecture

### 3.6 Potential Challenges and Opportunities

**Challenges:**
- Requires stable internet connectivity for real-time data transmission
- Sensor calibration and testing needed to ensure accurate readings
- Fixed 50°C threshold may require adjustment depending on the environment
- System requires continuous power supply

**Opportunities:**
- Low-cost implementation makes the solution accessible to many sectors
- Growing demand for IoT-based safety systems in industrial and commercial environments
- Architecture can be expanded to support smoke, flame, and humidity sensors
- Future AI integration can improve prediction and early risk detection
- Multi-location monitoring can be added to support large facilities

